summary: Tested all AI Hub features: backend APIs and frontend code. All backend APIs pass. Frontend redirects to login (Google OAuth) so UI testing done via code review.
passed_tests: GET /api/hub/personas - Returns 8 personas with correct structure (id, name, description, category, emoji, active). Neo (Default) marked active=true
GET /api/hub/agents - Returns 35 agents with 25 industries and 4 frameworks arrays
GET /api/hub/agents?q=finance - Filters correctly, returns 3 agents (Automated Trading Bot, Stock Analysis Tool, Finance Agent)
Frontend App.js has /hub route pointing to HubPage component
SetupPage has data-testid='hub-nav-button' at line ~311 with onClick navigate('/hub')
HubPage has 3 tabs: Persona Library (tab-personas), Agent Directory (tab-agents), LLM Providers (tab-providers)
HubPage has hub-back-btn that navigates to '/'
HubPage personas tab: renders persona-card-{id} for each persona
HubPage agents tab: has agent-search input, industry-filter and framework-filter select dropdowns
HubPage providers tab: has provider-card-emergent, provider-card-anthropic, provider-card-openai and kimi-provider-card
Hub /hub route redirects to /login when unauthenticated (correct behavior)
context_for_next_testing_agent: All AI Hub features implemented and working. Backend APIs: /api/hub/personas (8 personas), /api/hub/agents (35 agents with search/filter). Frontend: /hub route with HubPage, hub-nav-button on SetupPage. Auth required for hub page (redirects to /login if not logged in). Google OAuth prevents browser automation of authenticated flows.
